foot on my watch,

316
00:17:40,477 --> 00:17:42,393
I've got a mountain
of paperwork.

317
00:17:42,495 --> 00:17:45,596
On top of that, I promised to
try and get out of here in time

318
00:17:45,698 --> 00:17:47,665
to see my son in his
Halloween costume.

319
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:50,351
Is Tuck even old enough
to know what Halloween is?

320
00:17:50,453 --> 00:17:54,388
He's not, but his father is,
and that's who I promised.

321
00:17:55,290 --> 00:17:57,057
Trick or treat!

322
00:18:01,030 --> 00:18:03,830
For ears? He's trick
or treating for ears?

323
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:06,333
Yeah. Could you also persuade

324
00:18:06,435 --> 00:18:08,936
some of the surgical
nurses to help out?

325
00:18:09,038 --> 00:18:11,855
They seem to really like you.

326
00:18:11,957 --> 00:18:14,308
- Trick or treat.
- Stop that.

327
00:18:16,729 --> 00:18:18,495
All right. I'm in.

328
00:18:28,408 --> 00:18:30,908
She's warm. It
doesn't make sense.

329
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:33,193
I'm sorry.

330
00:18:33,295 --> 00:18:36,964
She's breathing with
the help of machines.

331
00:18:37,066 --> 00:18:42,636
Erin, the person that you
knew, isn't there anymore.

332
00:18:50,679 --> 00:18:54,165
Um, would you
bring this paperwork?

333
00:18:54,684 --> 00:18:56,350
Mm-hmm.

334
00:18:56,452 --> 00:18:57,951
You can have her.

335
00:18:58,053 --> 00:19:01,922
You can have her organs.
That's what she wanted.

336
00:19:02,024 --> 00:19:04,074
And her heart?

337
00:19:06,929 --> 00:19:09,630
Give it to someone else.

338
00:19:13,335 --> 00:19:15,770
