and Sydney Heron.

345
00:19:32,955 --> 00:19:35,122
I need to put my mother to rest.

346
00:19:35,224 --> 00:19:36,323
Sydney Heron?

347
00:19:51,758 --> 00:19:53,373
Just ask.

348
00:19:55,210 --> 00:19:58,478
- So, you two are together?
- Yeah.

349
00:19:58,580 --> 00:19:59,863
Like, together-together?

350
00:19:59,965 --> 00:20:02,567
In love together? Sexy
love, not sibling love.

351
00:20:03,585 --> 00:20:06,020
Yes. Yeah. We're together.

352
00:20:06,923 --> 00:20:09,806
And you two have been...

353
00:20:09,908 --> 00:20:11,886
I mean, without
any of us knowing...

354
00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:14,122
doing this the whole time?

355
00:20:14,146 --> 00:20:15,746
- Just once.
- Iz.

356
00:20:15,848 --> 00:20:17,998
I said she could ask questions.

357
00:20:19,501 --> 00:20:21,218
Just once.

358
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:25,156
And now we're
waiting to be together.

359
00:20:25,258 --> 00:20:27,541
- Out of respect.
- For Callie's feelings.

360
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:37,434
- She's not judging.
- Right.

361
00:20:41,924 --> 00:20:44,925
I have an earless
boy waiting for me.

362
00:20:45,027 --> 00:20:49,713
But... I'm happy for you guys.

363
00:20:59,692 --> 00:21:01,859
- Norman.
- Do you have to go?

364
00:21:01,961 --> 00:21:06,029
No. Norman can get by for a
few more minutes without me.

365
00:21:07,967 --> 00:21:11,284
How are you? I mean,
how have you been?

366
00:21:11,386 --> 00:21:16,106
I'm in love with my daughter.
She's perfect. She's...

367
00:21:16,208 --> 00:21:18,175
