368
00:21:18,278 --> 00:21:21,078
It's her new thing...
and she makes like this,

369
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:24,915
perfect little cartoon
suckling sound.

370
00:21:25,818 --> 00:21:27,434
And your husband?

371
00:21:29,304 --> 00:21:32,439
My husband's in love
with my daughter too.

372
00:21:35,711 --> 00:21:39,813
- You look tired.
- I haven't been sleeping much.

373
00:21:39,915 --> 00:21:42,027
I haven't been
sleeping much either.

374
00:21:42,051 --> 00:21:44,051
The baby wakes up all the time.

375
00:21:45,070 --> 00:21:47,299
Not as much now
that I figured out

376
00:21:47,323 --> 00:21:50,073
that if I wrap her in
whatever shirt I'm wearing...

377
00:21:50,175 --> 00:21:52,692
Hmm. She smells you. Yeah.

378
00:21:52,795 --> 00:21:55,695
Yeah. She sleeps.

379
00:21:56,899 --> 00:22:00,534
Alex, what are we doing?

380
00:22:00,636 --> 00:22:03,620
I mean, what are we going to do?

381
00:22:04,523 --> 00:22:05,790
Hmm.

382
00:22:15,968 --> 00:22:18,385
Dr. Hahn. Thank you for
coming on such short notice.

383
00:22:18,487 --> 00:22:22,857
Oh, not a problem. Are we harvesting the
heart for UNOS or is the recipient here?

384
00:22:22,959 --> 00:22:26,510
I'm hoping the recipient is
here, but he hasn't agreed yet.

385
00:22:26,612 --> 00:22:31,148
I've never had much trouble talking
a heart patient into taking a heart.

386
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:35,553
- It's his daughter's heart.
- OK.

387
00:22:35,655 --> 00:22:39,423
- Get him to OR two
and page Torres.
- OK. Where are you going?

388
00:22:39,525 --> 00:22:43,077
- Hey. What's Hahn doing here?
- She's been declared
brain dead.

389
00:22:43,179 --> 00:22:45,295
Heart transplant. Don't
even think about it.

390
00:22:45,398 --> 00:22:47,047
- It's my patient.
- Dr. Hahn.

391
00:22:47,149 --> 00:22:48,682
You're doing a heart transplant,

392
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:50,517
I thought I'd
volunteer to scrub in.

393
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:53,136
Isobel Stevens. She's
my patient, the donor.

394
00:22:53,239 --> 00:22:55,656
So if you need any
information, I have it. All of it.

395
00:22:55,758 --> 00:22:57,090
She's my patient.

396
00:22:57,192 --> 00:23:00,393
You've got some eager
junior residents around here.

397
00:23:00,496 --> 00:23:01,995
Lucky me.

398
00:23:02,097 --> 00:23:03,697
Take your pick.

399
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:07,935
Well, Yang, I appreciate
the offer, but I date men.

400
00:23:08,037 --> 00:23:09,797
So I don't think
you'll impress me

401
00:23:09,821 --> 00:23:12,456
the way you've impressed
your mentors in the past.

402
00:23:12,558 --> 00:23:14,508
I... What?

403
00:23:14,610 --> 00:23:18,962
You sleep with them, right? Preston
Burke, Colin Marlowe. That's your thing?

404
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:21,915
It's my... It's... I'm...

405
00:23:22,018 --> 00:23:25,002
I'm sorry... What does that
have to do with anything?

406
00:23:25,104 --> 00:23:28,072
My theory is, if you
had the chops in the OR,

407
00:23:28,174 --> 00:23:31,391
you wouldn't need to try
to impress in the bedroom.

408
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:33,277
- Stevens, is it?
- It is.

409
00:23:33,379 --> 00:23:35,045
Let's go, Stevens.

410
00:23:41,220 --> 00:23:42,486
Well, I bust my ass here,

411
00:23:42,588 --> 00:23:45,255
Burke skips town with
my cardio reputation...

412
00:23:45,357 --> 00:23:46,940
So instead of a
heart transplant,

413
00:23:47,043 --> 00:23:48,923
I get to participate
in the amputation

414
00:23:49,011 --> 00:23:50,455
- of a crazy man's foot.
- I'm not...

415
00:23:50,479 --> 00:23:53,363
Crazy. Cutting off
your foot is crazy.

416
00:23:53,465 --> 00:23:55,782
Walking through your
life like you have no power,

417
00:23:55,884 --> 00:23:57,518
like you have no say...

418
00:23:57,619 --> 00:23:59,769
No say in your own destiny.

419
00:23:59,871 --> 00:24:02,639
Like you have no control
over your own body.

420
00:24:02,741 --> 00:24:06,126
Walking through life
like that is what's crazy.

421
00:24:07,396 --> 00:24:09,508
I still think it's
cutting off your foot

422
00:24:09,532 --> 00:24:11,198
with a chainsaw that's crazy.

423
00:24:14,353 --> 00:24:17,254
Mr. Shanley, I'm Dr. Hahn.

424
00:24:17,356 --> 00:24:22,659
The transplant team is in place
if you're ready to say goodbye.

425
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:27,848
- You must not have children.
- I'm sorry?

426
00:24:27,950 --> 00:24:30,384
If you had children,
you'd never say that.

427
00:24:30,486 --> 00:24:33,320
You'd never say, "If you're
ready to say goodbye."

428
00:24:35,407 --> 00:24:37,641
Mr. Shanley, I'm very sorry.

429
00:24:37,743 --> 00:24:42,479
- But I want to suggest
one last time...
- No! I'm not taking her heart.

430
00:24:42,581 --> 00:24:45,415
I can't have my daughter's
heart beating in my chest.

431
00:24:45,517 --> 00:24:47,884
It would haunt me
every day of my life. No!

432
00:24:47,986 --> 00:24:52,973
All right. I'm very
sorry for your loss.

433
00:24:54,944 --> 00:24:57,077
Page me when he's ready.

434
00:25:03,101 --> 00:25:05,402
Mr. Shanley?

435
00:25:05,504 --> 00:25:09,089
I don't have kids, so I don't
know what it's like to lose a child,

436
00:25:09,191 --> 00:25:12,109
but I do know what
it's like to lose a parent.

437
00:25:12,211 --> 00:25:14,812
Your daughter loved
you. I saw her this morning.

438
00:25:14,914 --> 00:25:16,881
She was fighting for you.

439
00:25:16,983 --> 00:25:20,017
She was fighting for your life.

440
00:25:20,119 --> 00:25:22,369
You're her dad.

441
00:25:22,471 --> 00:25:25,121
You're her dad... she
didn't want to leave you.

442
00:25:25,223 --> 00:25:27,074
I know that.

443
00:25:27,176 --> 00:25:31,045
I also know that she would
want you to have her heart.

444
00:25:37,085 --> 00:25:40,587
I would've given my
dad my heart if I could.

445
00:25:42,458 --> 00:25:46,326
If I could have saved him...

446
00:25:46,428 --> 00:25:49,346
I would have given him my heart.

447
00:26:04,263 --> 00:26:06,329
All right.

448
00:26:12,938 --> 00:26:15,439
- It's not my fault
Hahn chose me.
- Whatever.

449
00:26:15,541 --> 00:26:17,575
I can't believe that
you are judging me.

450
00:26:17,677 --> 00:26:20,427
After what Hahn said to
you, that you are judging me.

451
00:26:20,529 --> 00:26:23,330
- It's not the same thing.
- It is the same thing.

452
00:26:23,432 --> 00:26:26,300
It's exactly the same thing.

453
00:26:26,402 --> 00:26:29,836
I'm sorry that I hurt Callie.
I didn't mean to hurt her.

454
00:26:29,938 --> 00:26:33,139
You slept with her husband.
I slept with my boyfriend.

455
00:26:33,242 --> 00:26:34,574
It's not the same thing.

456
00:26:34,676 --> 00:26:38,144
Meredith slept with
another woman's husband.

457
00:26:38,246 --> 00:26:41,047
Meredith slept with
another woman's husband!

458
00:26:41,149 --> 00:26:43,366
The two of you are
like this closed circle.

459
00:26:43,469 --> 00:26:47,471
You can commit whatever crime you
want, in your little circle, it's all fine.

460
00:26:47,573 --> 00:26:51,742
I... I know that you didn't
sleep with Burke to get ahead.

461
00:26:51,844 --> 00:26:55,762
And if Hahn had asked
me, I would've defended you.

462
00:26:55,864 --> 00:26:57,931
I'm not even asking
you to defend me.

463
00:26:58,033 --> 00:27:00,751
I'm asking you to just
cut me an inch of slack.

464
00:27:00,853 --> 00:27:05,439
And believe me when I say
that I am sorry I hurt Callie.

465
00:27:07,176 --> 00:27:08,992
We are not a closed circle.

466
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:12,613
You are.

467
00:27:18,620 --> 00:27:20,100
- Dr. Shepherd.
- Yes.

468
00:27:20,189 --> 00:27:22,956
Were there actual
shepherds in your lineage?

469
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:24,338
I'm sorry, what?

470
00:27:24,376 --> 00:27:27,327
Shepherds, ones who watch
over sheep. I'm into genealogy.

471
00:27:27,429 --> 00:27:29,963
My name, for example,
not actually after the bird.

472
00:27:30,065 --> 00:27:31,709
I'm sorry. Would you excuse me?

473
00:27:31,733 --> 00:27:33,967
- Of course.
- OK. Thank you.

474
00:27:34,069 --> 00:27:35,969
- You did this.
- Payback's a bitch.

475
00:27:36,072 --> 00:27:39,473
- What the hell'd you tell her?
- I put the word out
that you're lookin'.

476
00:27:39,575 --> 00:27:41,558
- That I'm looking?
- Lookin'.

477
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:45,228
- Sounds dirtier without the G.
- You wonder why
they formed a club?

478
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:48,315
- You heard about that?
- Yeah.

479
00:27:48,417 --> 00:27:51,118
OK. So we have
one plastic surgeon.

480
00:27:51,220 --> 00:27:53,720
A general surgeon.
An anesthesiologist.

